# Commit messages

Piper enforces [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) via Husky + Commitlint. Full human docs: [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md).

## When creating a git commit

1. Use format: `<type>(<optional-scope>): <description>`
2. Description: **lower-case**, imperative mood, **no** trailing period
3. Header â‰¤ 100 chars; body lines â‰¤ 100 chars
4. Prefer one logical change per commit
5. Pass the message via HEREDOC (never `-i` interactive git)

### Allowed types

`feat` Â· `fix` Â· `docs` Â· `style` Â· `refactor` Â· `perf` Â· `test` Â· `build` Â· `ci` Â· `chore` Â· `revert`

### Allowed scopes (optional)

`auth` Â· `bots` Â· `chat` Â· `cron` Â· `db` Â· `feed` Â· `realtime` Â· `ui` Â· `api` Â· `deps` Â· `release`

If you need a new scope, update `commitlint.config.mjs` and `CONTRIBUTING.md` in the same change.

### Good

```text
feat(chat): add floating mini-dock for bot conversations
fix(realtime): uniquify channel names to avoid subscribe collision
docs: add contributing guide for conventional commits
```

### Bad

```text
Update stuff
Fixed bug.
feat(Chat): Add Mini Dock.
feat(messages): new inbox
```

(`messages` is not an allowed scope â€” use `chat`.)

## Do not

- Skip hooks (`--no-verify`) unless the user explicitly asks
- Commit `.env.local` or secrets
- Invent commit types outside the enum
